UAE Board::BIM Manager
BIM Manager Management
BIM Manager for contracting company in Abu DhabiThe Role: This position is a hands-on role that requires significant experience in planning, organizing, controlling and managing a multi-discipline technical office for Engineering & Architecture Services for the company projects. This role requires people, systems and detail construction management experience, communications skills and a positive attitude.
You will: Coordinate, manage and assist in directing engineering technical submittals and projects construction to accomplish projects goals. Analyze engineering resource requirements and coordinate the staffing levels to ensure smooth and uninterrupted construction activities. Coordinate the recruitment of construction staff; assign, direct, and evaluate their work; and oversee the development and maintenance of staff competence. Develop and implement policies, standards and procedures for engineering technical submittals and projects construction and allied work performed in the technical department. Perform administrative functions such as reviewing and writing reports, approving expenditures, enforcing policy, and making decisions about the purchase of materials or services. Review and recommend or approve contracts and proposal cost and effort estimates. Consult or negotiate with clients to consider project specifications alternatives. Set and achieve technical goals (Efficiency, Quality, Sustainability, HSE, etc) within broad outlines provided by top management To perform the job successfully you will possess the following:
Education: A Bachelor of Science Degree in Architecture with outstanding experience with BIM and REVIT.Email CV to: careers@ams.ae
